    • Constructor Detail

      • TAG_CA_CODEC

        public TAG_CA_CODEC()
        Create an object that holds a null TAG_CA_CODEC.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          TAG_CA_CODEC obj = new TAG_CA_CODEC();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new TAG_CA_CODEC, use the static "constructor" : 
          TAG_CA_CODEC obj = TAG_CA_CODEC.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

    • Method Detail

      • asTAG_CA_CODEC

        public static TAG_CA_CODEC asTAG_CA_CODEC(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a TAG_CA_CODEC object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a TAG_CA_CODEC object.
